MOORE v. WARDEN OF MARYLAND PENITENTIARY [App. No. 136,

September Term, 1963.]

Decided April 27, 1964.

Before the entire Court.

Per Curiam.

The application of James Ed. Moore for leave to appeal from the order denying him post conviction relief from his imprison*639ment for armed robbery is hereby denied for the reasons stated in the opinion delivered by Judge Menchine in the lower court.

Application denied.
